UID:gUCk-AlEq_0MpaFPBTHtK
SUMMARY:Free Tax Help
DTSTAMP:20260413T004139Z
DTSTART:20260415T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Wednesday\, April 15\, 2026\, 12:30 - 6:30pm\n\nTrained volunte
	ers will be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns
	.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom Location: Level 5 - Mixing 
	Chamber Meeting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not require
	d.\n\nDetailed Description: Drop-in tax help is offered on a first-come\, 
	first-served basis.\, This service is free and available to individuals on
	ly.\, The free service is not available for business tax returns.\, To rec
	eive tax help\, bring the following documents:\,\n\nRequired Documents:\n\
	nPhoto identification\, Social Security cards or Individual Taxpayer Ident
	ification Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for everyone listed on the tax return\, Proof
	 of income\, for example\, W2s and 1099s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, 
	Official documents on Social Security Administration letterhead\, Medicare
	 card \\(if Social Security number is followed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared 
	to provide information about health care coverage for each person on the r
	eturn\,\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast year's tax return\, if available\, Bank ac
	count and routing numbers for direct deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or c
	omputer print-outs of any of these documents will be accepted.\, Due to fe
	deral budget cuts the IRS is unable to provide the Library with certain ta
	x forms and instruction booklets.\, Most IRS forms are available online at
	\n\nwww.irs.gov. \, You may make free black-and-white prints of the forms 
	from Library computers:\n\nwww.spl.org/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nU
	nited Way of King County .\n\nEvent Logistics: United Way Tax Help locatio
	ns serve anyone who earned less than $80\,000 in 2025 \\(or less than $96\
	,000 for non-single filers\\).\, For eligibility details\, contact United 
	Way at 206-461-3700.\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event
	\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provid
	e accommodations for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\
	ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodat
	ions.\, All Library programs are free and open to the public.\,\n\nhttps:/
	/seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/2026-04-15T0
	0\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/20
	26-04-15T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
